com.guardtime.ksi.service.ha

Class ExtendingHAService

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.guardtime.ksi.service.ha.ExtendingHAService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    KSIExtendingService, Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public class ExtendingHAService
extends Object
implements KSIExtendingService
    KSI Extending Service which combines clients to achieve redundancy. NB! It is highly recommended that all the extender configurations would be in sync with each other (except credentials), but if this is not the case then the configurations will be consolidated in an optimistic manner which means that if a configuration parameter would improve how user can consume the service then it's preferred in the consolidated configuration.

      • extend

        public Future<ExtensionResponse> extend(Date aggregationTime,
                                        Date publicationTime)
                                 throws KSIException
        Creates a non-blocking extending request. Sends the request to all the subservices in parallel. First successful response is used, others are cancelled. Request fails only if all the subservices fail.
        Specified by:
        extend in interface KSIExtendingService
        Parameters:
        aggregationTime - aggregation time of the existing signature.
        publicationTime - publication time to which the existing signature is to be extended.
        Returns:
        Instance of ExtensionResponseFuture containing calendar chains needed to extend the signature.
        Throws:
        KSIException - in case any error occurs.
        See Also:
        KSIExtendingService.extend(Date, Date)

      • getSubExtendingServices

        public List<KSIExtendingService> getSubExtendingServices()
        Description copied from interface: KSIExtendingService
        Gets the subclients in case of the implementation that combines multiple clients. If the implementation is a client that directly connects to a single gateway, an empty list will be returned.
        Specified by:

      • registerExtenderConfigurationListener

        public void registerExtenderConfigurationListener(ConfigurationListener<ExtenderConfiguration> listener)
        Registers configuration listeners that will be called if this ExtendingHAService's configuration changes. They will not be called if subservice's configuration changes in a way that does not change the consolidated configuration. To get detailed info about subservices' configurations one should register their own listeners directly on subservices. Listener will be called instantaneously once with the latest consolidation result as part of the registration if the latest result is not null.
        Specified by:
        registerExtenderConfigurationListener in interface KSIExtendingService
        Parameters:
        listener - may not be null.

      • getExtendingConfiguration

        public Future<ExtenderConfiguration> getExtendingConfiguration()
        Invokes a configuration for all the subservices. Does not block until responses are received. Active configuration listeners are only called if any of the responses change the state of consolidated configuration.
        Specified by:
        getExtendingConfiguration in interface KSIExtendingService
        Returns:
        A future of the result. Can be used as an alternative to listeners to access the configuration result.
